---
import "./baseline.css";
---

<div class="demo baseline-demo">
  <div class="baseline-demo-inner">
    <p>
      Every line of this paragraph rests on the baseline grid painted behind it.
      The bolder lines mark a full line of text; the fainter ones mark the
      baseline step, a third of a line. Because the line height and every vertical
      space are built from the same unit, the text stays locked to the beat.
    </p>
    <p>
      Change the root line height and the whole grid, and the text on it, rescales
      together.
    </p>
  </div>
</div>
